35
00:01:27.149 --> 00:01:30.718
♪ cold and dark.
below the foam ♪

36
00:01:30.786 --> 00:01:33.721
♪ they wait for us
but never... ♪

37
00:01:38.494 --> 00:01:39.994
Supper's ready.

38
00:02:10.993 --> 00:02:13.060
Lucassi said he found
the body on the beach

39
00:02:13.128 --> 00:02:14.862
early this morning.

40
00:02:18.500 --> 00:02:20.334
Lucassi?

41
00:02:20.402 --> 00:02:21.803
Nathan.

42
00:02:21.870 --> 00:02:23.070
What you got?

43
00:02:23.138 --> 00:02:25.640
Came out to do some clamming.

44
00:02:25.707 --> 00:02:27.835
Found this instead.

45
00:02:30.646 --> 00:02:32.246
I already got a liver temp.

46
00:02:32.314 --> 00:02:33.247
He's been dead
about ten hours.

47
00:02:33.315 --> 00:02:34.782
Who is he?

48
00:02:34.850 --> 00:02:37.285
I don't know. I was about
to check for some I.D.

49
00:02:37.352 --> 00:02:38.653
Nathan.

50
00:02:38.720 --> 00:02:40.555
Well. we've seen
that before.

51
00:02:40.622 --> 00:02:42.123
There's no wallet.

52
00:02:42.191 --> 00:02:46.627
Just this.

53
00:02:46.695 --> 00:02:48.329
He had a wife. maybe?

54
00:02:48.397 --> 00:02:49.864
Yeah. or a girlfriend.

55
00:02:49.932 --> 00:02:52.033
Either way. someone
who can I.D. him.

56
00:02:52.100 --> 00:02:54.635
Oh. I got something else.

57
00:02:54.703 --> 00:02:56.137
This handwritten note.

58
00:02:56.205 --> 00:02:57.371
Not much left.

59
00:02:57.439 --> 00:03:00.141
"I'm sorry to
leave you like this.

60
00:03:00.209 --> 00:03:04.111
I know it will hurt.
but I can't go on."

61
00:03:04.179 --> 00:03:05.746
Suicide note.

62
00:03:05.814 --> 00:03:07.121
Wouldn't be the first guy
around here

63
00:03:07.241 --> 00:03:08.449
to go for
a one-way swim.

64
00:03:08.483 --> 00:03:11.953
Well...

65
00:03:12.020 --> 00:03:15.756
Maybe this woman
can tell us why.

66
00:03:17.559 --> 00:03:19.160
I heard you pulled a body
out of the water

67
00:03:19.228 --> 00:03:20.828
near Benny's Cove.

68
00:03:20.896 --> 00:03:23.865
What. are you worried
he left an open bar tab?

69
00:03:23.932 --> 00:03:25.533
No.

70
00:03:25.601 --> 00:03:27.301
Actually. I more concerned
about the tattoo he had on him.

71
00:03:27.369 --> 00:03:31.205
How did you know
he had a tattoo?

72
00:03:31.273 --> 00:03:34.308
Truce!

73
00:03:34.376 --> 00:03:38.646
Do you know him?

74
00:03:38.714 --> 00:03:40.882
No. Who is he?

75
00:03:40.949 --> 00:03:42.683
If I knew. then
I wouldn't have asked you.

76
00:03:42.751 --> 00:03:44.185
Nobody recognizes him?

77
00:03:44.253 --> 00:03:45.586
Nope.

78
00:03:45.654 --> 00:03:48.389
Nathan. I need to know
who this guy is. okay?

79
00:03:48.457 --> 00:03:50.358
What if he's the guy
who's supposed to kill me?

80
00:03:50.425 --> 00:03:51.959
Duke. if I find out
anything pertinent

81
00:03:52.027 --> 00:03:53.561
relating to
your imminent demise.

82
00:03:53.629 --> 00:03:54.929
then I will let you know.

83
00:03:54.997 --> 00:03:56.564
I found out
the woman in the key chain photo

84
00:03:56.632 --> 00:03:58.232
is Mary Collins.

85
00:03:58.300 --> 00:03:59.333
I guess she runs
the soup kitchen

86
00:03:59.401 --> 00:04:00.835
at Reverend Driscoll's church.

87
00:04:00.903 --> 00:04:02.737
Reverend Driscoll's involved?

88
00:04:02.804 --> 00:04:05.439
- Out. now.
- Okay.

89
00:04:05.507 --> 00:04:06.741
And stay out of this

90
00:04:06.808 --> 00:04:08.242
or you're gonna be asking
your cell mate

91
00:04:08.310 --> 00:04:10.444
what he knows about tattoos.

92
00:04:10.512 --> 00:04:12.079
- You hear that?
- Mm.

93
00:04:12.147 --> 00:04:14.515
What do you think of that?

94
00:04:19.821 --> 00:04:21.422
Leith's been on edge
the past few weeks.

95
00:04:21.490 --> 00:04:22.957
but I can't believe...

96
00:04:23.025 --> 00:04:24.358
You sure it's him?

97
00:04:24.426 --> 00:04:25.593
Mm-hm.

98
00:04:25.661 --> 00:04:29.063
We found the body
this morning.

99
00:04:29.131 --> 00:04:31.265
Leith had a rather
unusual tattoo.

100
00:04:31.333 --> 00:04:32.667
Family thing.

101
00:04:32.734 --> 00:04:34.802
Not just Leith.
a lot of the Glendowers have it.

102
00:04:34.870 --> 00:04:36.137
Did Leith give you any idea

103
00:04:36.204 --> 00:04:37.371
what may have
been bothering him?

104
00:04:37.439 --> 00:04:39.373
Why he'd commit suicide?

105
00:04:39.441 --> 00:04:40.841
Money.

106
00:04:40.909 --> 00:04:42.476
He knew things
were tight for us.

107
00:04:42.544 --> 00:04:45.446
I mean. even though
we weren't together anymore.

108
00:04:45.514 --> 00:04:47.114
he tried to give me money
for me and Daniel.

109
00:04:47.182 --> 00:04:48.616
Our son.

110
00:04:48.684 --> 00:04:50.952
He's only ten.

111
00:04:51.019 --> 00:04:56.290
How do I tell him
that his father's dead?

112
00:04:56.358 --> 00:04:57.959
The Glendowers
live in a compound

113
00:04:58.026 --> 00:04:59.193
beyond the outskirts of town.

114
00:04:59.261 --> 00:05:00.962
There's no paved roads
in or out.

115
00:05:01.029 --> 00:05:03.998
A lot of people are afraid
to even go there.

116
00:05:04.066 --> 00:05:05.199
You make it sound like

117
00:05:05.267 --> 00:05:07.835
Leith's family's
some kind of cult.

118
00:05:07.903 --> 00:05:09.971
A lot of people around here
think they are.

119
00:05:10.038 --> 00:05:11.605
My dad would drive out there.

120
00:05:11.673 --> 00:05:14.108
check on them
every once in a while.

121
00:05:14.176 --> 00:05:15.142
I even went with him
a few times

122
00:05:15.210 --> 00:05:16.644
when I was a kid.

123
00:05:16.712 --> 00:05:20.014
- Are they troubled?
- My dad never said anything.

124
00:05:20.082 --> 00:05:22.283
- Not that he would.
- Hmm.

125
00:05:22.351 --> 00:05:25.586
The school said Leith didn't
drop Daniel off at school.

126
00:05:25.654 --> 00:05:26.821
I tried calling
Daniel's cell phone.

127
00:05:26.888 --> 00:05:28.222
but he wasn't picking up.

128
00:05:28.290 --> 00:05:30.024
You don't think
that Leith took Daniel

129
00:05:30.092 --> 00:05:31.559
and they're both dead?

130
00:05:31.626 --> 00:05:33.294
Okay. when was the last time
that you saw Daniel?

131
00:05:33.362 --> 00:05:34.695
Yesterday.

132
00:05:34.763 --> 00:05:36.297
Leith dropped him off
at his family's place

133
00:05:36.365 --> 00:05:37.665
for the night.

134
00:05:37.733 --> 00:05:39.967
Daniel likes hanging out
with his cousins.

135
00:05:40.035 --> 00:05:41.168
He's been going back and forth
until Leith and I

136
00:05:41.236 --> 00:05:42.303
can settle custody.

137
00:05:42.371 --> 00:05:43.304
I need you to stay at home

138
00:05:43.372 --> 00:05:44.305
in case he turns up there.

139
00:05:44.373 --> 00:05:45.940
Listen. don't worry.

140
00:05:46.008 --> 00:05:48.209
We're gonna find him.

141
00:06:07.029 --> 00:06:09.363
It's not what I expected.

142
00:06:09.431 --> 00:06:11.032
Back when I would
visit with my dad

143
00:06:11.099 --> 00:06:13.267
there were always tons
of kids my age running around.

144
00:06:13.335 --> 00:06:15.336
Well. maybe they're in school.

145
00:06:15.404 --> 00:06:17.538
- No. they were
all home-schooled.

146
00:06:17.606 --> 00:06:19.740
I always thought
that was kind of cool.

147
00:06:19.808 --> 00:06:22.510
Maybe Daniel
feels the same way.

148
00:06:22.577 --> 00:06:25.346
Nathan.

149
00:06:25.414 --> 00:06:26.814
It's been a long time.

150
00:06:26.882 --> 00:06:28.182
Cole.

151
00:06:28.250 --> 00:06:31.018
We were sorry to hear
about your father.

152
00:06:31.086 --> 00:06:33.687
This is Officer Parker.

153
00:06:33.755 --> 00:06:37.124
This is Gwen
and Cole Glendower.

154
00:06:40.395 --> 00:06:44.231
It's nice to meet you.

155
00:06:44.299 --> 00:06:45.666
Why are you here?

156
00:06:45.734 --> 00:06:48.702
We found Leith
on a beach outside town.

157
00:06:48.770 --> 00:06:50.004
He's dead.

158
00:06:50.072 --> 00:06:52.540
I'm sorry.

159
00:06:52.607 --> 00:06:54.175
Looks like suicide.

160
00:06:54.242 --> 00:06:56.844
Suicide?

161
00:06:56.912 --> 00:06:57.845
Are you sure?

162
00:06:57.913 --> 00:07:00.114
We found this on him.

163
00:07:00.182 --> 00:07:03.617
Can you tell me
anything about it?

164
00:07:04.853 --> 00:07:06.487
No.

165
00:07:10.192 --> 00:07:11.992
Mary said Daniel was here.

166
00:07:12.060 --> 00:07:13.994
We've come to take him home.

167
00:07:14.062 --> 00:07:16.297
Daniel's place is with us.

168
00:07:16.364 --> 00:07:18.399
now that his father has died.

169
00:07:18.467 --> 00:07:19.967
We'll tell the poor boy
what happened.

170
00:07:20.035 --> 00:07:21.602
That's up to his mother.

171
00:07:21.670 --> 00:07:23.504
No. Mary can't
take care of Daniel.

172
00:07:23.572 --> 00:07:26.307
That's why we were
trying to get custody.

173
00:07:26.374 --> 00:07:27.741
We?
I thought that was Leith.

174
00:07:27.809 --> 00:07:29.844
Leith was a Glendower.

175
00:07:29.911 --> 00:07:32.146
Where's Daniel?

176
00:07:32.214 --> 00:07:33.881
And for that matter.

177
00:07:33.949 --> 00:07:35.816
where are any
of the children?

178
00:07:35.884 --> 00:07:38.853
I thought you
home-schooled. right?

179
00:07:38.920 --> 00:07:41.655
I'm not gonna ask
again. Cole.

180
00:07:41.723 --> 00:07:44.258
Where's Daniel?

181
00:07:44.326 --> 00:07:47.428
We're not answering
any more questions.

182
00:07:47.496 --> 00:07:48.629
Your father was a friend to us.

183
00:07:48.697 --> 00:07:50.764
but it's time for
you both to leave.

184
00:07:50.832 --> 00:07:52.800
Either you give us Daniel.

185
00:07:52.868 --> 00:07:54.468
or I'll get a warrant.

186
00:07:54.536 --> 00:07:58.139
And we'll have officers crawling
over every inch of this place.

187
00:07:58.206 --> 00:07:59.173
Well. you make sure
you have that warrant

188
00:07:59.241 --> 00:08:02.877
next time I see you here.

189
00:08:17.926 --> 00:08:21.862
We're looking for Daniel.
Is he here?

190
00:08:21.930 --> 00:08:24.999
You can't have him.

191
00:08:25.066 --> 00:08:28.602
Daniel is one of us now.

192
00:08:37.212 --> 00:08:38.812
♪ ♪

193
00:08:39.164 --> 00:08:42.721
