195
00:09:09.177 --> 00:09:11.845
Let's get it together. guys.

196
00:09:24.626 --> 00:09:26.327
Reverend Driscoll
is helping me.

197
00:09:26.394 --> 00:09:27.861
We're going to get Daniel back.

198
00:09:27.929 --> 00:09:29.129
I thought I told you
to wait at home.

199
00:09:29.197 --> 00:09:30.664
I couldn't just sit there.

200
00:09:30.732 --> 00:09:33.033
The Glendowers
do have Daniel.

201
00:09:33.101 --> 00:09:35.336
Look what he texted me.

202
00:09:35.403 --> 00:09:37.204
He sent it with a message.
saying that he wants to

203
00:09:37.272 --> 00:09:39.240
live with them
and the other boys now.

204
00:09:39.307 --> 00:09:44.411
Those... those people
have brainwashed my son.

205
00:09:44.479 --> 00:09:47.014
You shouldn't have
involved Reverend Driscoll.

206
00:09:47.082 --> 00:09:48.949
He's helping me
get my son back.

207
00:09:49.017 --> 00:09:51.585
No one is going out
to the Glendowers'.

208
00:09:51.653 --> 00:09:54.989
You are trying to protect
the scum of the earth.

209
00:09:55.056 --> 00:09:57.324
What do you think you know
about the Glendowers?

210
00:09:57.392 --> 00:09:58.892
I know they're
the kind of filth

211
00:09:58.960 --> 00:10:02.963
that should have been cleansed
from this town years ago.

212
00:10:03.031 --> 00:10:05.092
Mary.

213
00:10:06.668 --> 00:10:08.135
You don't wanna do this.

214
00:10:08.203 --> 00:10:09.370
I want my son.

215
00:10:09.437 --> 00:10:10.671
You know how they feel
about outsiders.

216
00:10:10.739 --> 00:10:12.039
Storming over there
with a lynch mob

217
00:10:12.107 --> 00:10:13.507
isn't the way.

218
00:10:13.575 --> 00:10:15.109
I know you don't get along
with Leith's family.

219
00:10:15.176 --> 00:10:17.878
but they're
Daniel's family too.

220
00:10:17.946 --> 00:10:21.448
He's gonna need them
with his dad gone.

221
00:10:21.516 --> 00:10:23.851
They started this.

222
00:10:23.918 --> 00:10:26.920
Well. I'm sure they're
upset about Leith too.

223
00:10:31.459 --> 00:10:33.994
Let's do this the smart way.

224
00:10:40.168 --> 00:10:42.770
Pack it up.

225
00:10:42.837 --> 00:10:46.106
Mary wants you all to go home.

226
00:10:48.443 --> 00:10:50.577
All right. guys.

227
00:10:50.645 --> 00:10:53.580
We're not gonna
wait forever. Nathan!

228
00:10:53.648 --> 00:10:56.083
That boy's soul is at stake.

229
00:10:56.151 --> 00:10:59.253
I'll call you when
I have him.

230
00:11:05.694 --> 00:11:07.328
What on earth are these?

231
00:11:07.395 --> 00:11:08.796
The least
of our concerns.

232
00:11:08.863 --> 00:11:10.531
We need to find Daniel.

233
00:11:10.598 --> 00:11:12.032
The Rev and his men
are this close

234
00:11:12.100 --> 00:11:14.068
to going all <i>Mad Max</i>
on the Glendowers.

235
00:11:14.135 --> 00:11:15.969
I think I know why
he's interested.

236
00:11:16.037 --> 00:11:18.138
I found a case in 1983.

237
00:11:18.206 --> 00:11:20.841
A woman went missing.
Penny Driscoll.

238
00:11:20.909 --> 00:11:22.743
The Rev's wife.

239
00:11:22.811 --> 00:11:25.112
The suspect in the case.
your dad's prime suspect.

240
00:11:25.180 --> 00:11:27.748
Cole Glendower.

241
00:11:27.816 --> 00:11:29.083
Why did the chief
think Cole was involved?

242
00:11:29.150 --> 00:11:30.351
The report doesn't say.

243
00:11:30.418 --> 00:11:31.685
But then three days later.

244
00:11:31.753 --> 00:11:34.421
she was killed
in a car accident.

245
00:11:34.489 --> 00:11:36.023
The Rev thought it was murder.

246
00:11:36.091 --> 00:11:37.725
and your dad didn't pursue it.

247
00:11:37.792 --> 00:11:39.360
If the Rev thinks
Cole is responsible

248
00:11:39.427 --> 00:11:40.861
for his wife's death.

249
00:11:40.929 --> 00:11:43.464
that would explain
why he's looking for a fight.

250
00:11:43.531 --> 00:11:45.132
We don't find Daniel.
he's gonna turn that compound

251
00:11:45.200 --> 00:11:46.533
into a battleground.

252
00:11:46.601 --> 00:11:48.569
Then I say you and I
go out there tonight

253
00:11:48.636 --> 00:11:50.270
and we take an unofficial look.

254
00:11:50.338 --> 00:11:51.839
Last I checked.
breaking and entering

255
00:11:51.906 --> 00:11:52.873
was a felony.

256
00:11:52.941 --> 00:11:54.408
And last I checked.

257
00:11:54.476 --> 00:11:56.377
the troubles weren't
covered in the police manual.

258
00:11:56.444 --> 00:11:57.778
Look. I...

259
00:11:57.846 --> 00:11:59.580
I wanna do something.
but I'm the Chief now.

260
00:11:59.647 --> 00:12:00.781
I can't just...

261
00:12:00.849 --> 00:12:02.015
If the Glendowers
are troubled.

262
00:12:02.083 --> 00:12:03.250
like most of the people
we've met.

263
00:12:03.318 --> 00:12:05.219
they might not even
know about it.

264
00:12:05.286 --> 00:12:07.020
And if something happens
to Daniel.

265
00:12:07.088 --> 00:12:09.423
something happens
to those other children.

266
00:12:09.491 --> 00:12:10.591
and we could have
stopped it?

267
00:12:10.658 --> 00:12:12.826
We'll never forgive
ourselves.

268
00:12:12.894 --> 00:12:16.196
If I say "no." you're gonna
go out there anyway. aren't you?

269
00:12:16.264 --> 00:12:17.865
Come on.

270
00:12:17.932 --> 00:12:21.869
I bet you look good in black.

271
00:12:32.113 --> 00:12:33.547
Let's go.

272
00:12:37.819 --> 00:12:40.020
This one's locked.

273
00:12:40.088 --> 00:12:42.489
Okay.

274
00:12:42.557 --> 00:12:43.991
Picking and entering.

275
00:12:44.058 --> 00:12:45.692
Wow. that's better.

276
00:12:45.760 --> 00:12:48.228
Hey. none of the other houses
we searched were even locked.

277
00:12:48.296 --> 00:12:51.131
There's gotta
be a reason this one is.

278
00:12:51.199 --> 00:12:54.234
Hopefully Daniel
is in here somewhere.

279
00:13:41.149 --> 00:13:44.117
What'd you find?

280
00:13:44.185 --> 00:13:49.957
The reason Cole and Gwen
freaked out when they saw me.

281
00:13:50.024 --> 00:13:51.859
They knew Lucy Ripley?

282
00:13:54.229 --> 00:13:56.563
This man here?

283
00:13:56.631 --> 00:13:58.198
That's my dad.

284
00:13:58.266 --> 00:14:01.735
Chief knew Lucy?

285
00:14:01.803 --> 00:14:03.670
Why didn't he say anything?

286
00:14:09.944 --> 00:14:13.046
Sounds like someone
forgot to turn off the water.

287
00:14:49.584 --> 00:14:50.751
It's Daniel.

288
00:15:00.171 --> 00:15:01.704
Daniel?

289
00:15:01.772 --> 00:15:04.941
Are you okay?

290
00:15:06.610 --> 00:15:07.977
Get away from the boy!

291
00:15:08.045 --> 00:15:10.346
- What are you doing?
- What needs to be done.

292
00:15:10.414 --> 00:15:11.714
Move! Both of you!

293
00:15:17.655 --> 00:15:20.356
Back under the water.

294
00:15:20.424 --> 00:15:22.759
Daniel...

295
00:15:22.827 --> 00:15:24.260
Stop right there!

296
00:15:24.328 --> 00:15:26.262
Get away from him. Cole.

297
00:15:26.330 --> 00:15:27.897
I'm not gonna tell you again.

298
00:15:27.965 --> 00:15:29.866
You're the ones hurting him!

299
00:15:29.934 --> 00:15:32.569
Daniel. Come here.

300
00:15:32.636 --> 00:15:33.937
- Let me help...
- Let me go!

301
00:15:34.004 --> 00:15:35.939
Let me help you.
Daniel. stop! Stop!

302
00:15:36.006 --> 00:15:37.774
- Let me help you!
- No!

303
00:15:37.842 --> 00:15:39.042
No. wait!

304
00:15:39.109 --> 00:15:41.678
- Nathan. let him go.
- Huh? Why?

305
00:15:45.282 --> 00:15:48.351
I think that he needs
to go back under the water.

306
00:15:48.419 --> 00:15:49.853
All right?

307
00:15:49.920 --> 00:15:52.422
Please. just...

308
00:15:52.490 --> 00:15:53.723
Trust me.

309
00:15:53.791 --> 00:15:56.092
It's okay. Daniel.

310
00:15:56.160 --> 00:15:57.560
Lie down.

311
00:15:57.628 --> 00:15:59.062
Relax.

312
00:15:59.129 --> 00:16:02.599
It'll be all right.

313
00:16:15.112 --> 00:16:19.182
I thought you were
gonna make me dinner.

314
00:16:19.250 --> 00:16:23.086
Body washed up
on the beach today.

315
00:16:23.153 --> 00:16:25.421
Guy with a tattoo.

316
00:16:25.489 --> 00:16:27.090
Really? Did it say
"I heart Haven"?

317
00:16:29.927 --> 00:16:31.794
So...

318
00:16:31.862 --> 00:16:32.795
Who was he?

319
00:16:32.863 --> 00:16:35.131
I don't know yet.

320
00:16:35.199 --> 00:16:39.402
But I do know
that somehow he's tied

321
00:16:39.470 --> 00:16:41.004
to Reverend Driscoll.

322
00:16:41.071 --> 00:16:44.574
Well. maybe he knows
what that symbol means.

323
00:16:44.642 --> 00:16:46.809
Oh. I'm damn sure he does.

324
00:16:46.877 --> 00:16:49.646
The last time I asked him.
he just got all cryptic with me.

325
00:16:49.713 --> 00:16:52.115
Like. religious cryptic?

326
00:16:52.182 --> 00:16:53.616
Jackass cryptic.

327
00:16:53.684 --> 00:16:54.651
Oh.

328
00:16:54.718 --> 00:17:00.023
We don't exactly get along.

329
00:17:00.090 --> 00:17:03.092
But he hasn't met you yet.

330
00:17:06.764 --> 00:17:10.600
Daniel can only breathe air
for short periods of time now.

331
00:17:10.668 --> 00:17:12.168
- He's transitioning.
- Into what?

332
00:17:12.236 --> 00:17:16.105
For generations.
when the troubles come.

333
00:17:16.173 --> 00:17:18.608
AlI Glendower men.
young and old.

334
00:17:18.676 --> 00:17:20.677
lose their ability
to breathe air.

335
00:17:20.744 --> 00:17:21.911
How do you live?

336
00:17:21.979 --> 00:17:23.746
We migrate...

337
00:17:23.814 --> 00:17:26.249
to the sea.

338
00:17:26.317 --> 00:17:27.750
The children
are affected first.

339
00:17:27.818 --> 00:17:29.852
They need to breathe water
for a few hours every day

340
00:17:29.920 --> 00:17:31.120
as they change.

341
00:17:31.188 --> 00:17:33.222
But with Leith.
if this was happening.

342
00:17:33.290 --> 00:17:34.791
how could he drown?

343
00:17:34.858 --> 00:17:36.526
He may have panicked.
gone into the sea too soon.

344
00:17:36.594 --> 00:17:37.894
Mm-hm.

345
00:17:37.962 --> 00:17:41.764
It's why centuries ago.
we realized that

346
00:17:41.832 --> 00:17:44.033
on the ebb tide of a new moon.

347
00:17:44.101 --> 00:17:46.869
we had to all go
into the water together.

348
00:17:46.937 --> 00:17:52.508
Our unity triggers
the final transformation.

349
00:17:52.576 --> 00:17:54.177
Did my father
know about all this?

350
00:17:54.244 --> 00:17:55.545
Yes.

351
00:17:55.613 --> 00:17:58.514
At first we assumed
you did too. both of you.

352
00:18:04.021 --> 00:18:05.955
Because you recognized me.

353
00:18:06.023 --> 00:18:07.757
You thought that I was Lucy.

354
00:18:07.825 --> 00:18:09.292
But of course
that's impossible.

355
00:18:09.360 --> 00:18:11.928
Lucy would be in her 50s now.

356
00:18:11.996 --> 00:18:16.566
Daniel has to stay with us.

357
00:18:16.634 --> 00:18:19.068
The change happens
in two days!

358
00:18:19.136 --> 00:18:20.770
Why didn't Leith
just tell Mary

359
00:18:20.838 --> 00:18:21.771
what was happening?

360
00:18:21.839 --> 00:18:23.206
He was too afraid.

361
00:18:23.273 --> 00:18:25.408
She follows Reverend Driscoll.
and he believes

362
00:18:25.476 --> 00:18:26.442
that we're all evil.

363
00:18:26.510 --> 00:18:27.844
Particularly you.

364
00:18:27.911 --> 00:18:29.145
He thinks I killed his wife.

365
00:18:29.213 --> 00:18:30.446
Why?

366
00:18:30.514 --> 00:18:33.316
He discovered
we were having an affair.

367
00:18:33.384 --> 00:18:36.319
But I didn't kill her.

368
00:18:36.387 --> 00:18:37.854
Your father knew that. but...

369
00:18:37.921 --> 00:18:42.625
Reverend Driscoll
isn't a man to let anything go.

370
00:18:42.693 --> 00:18:45.261
Or anyone.

371
00:18:51.268 --> 00:18:55.104
It was 1983.

372
00:18:55.172 --> 00:18:58.408
The note we found
on Leith's body...

373
00:18:58.475 --> 00:19:00.410
You had seen it before.

374
00:19:00.477 --> 00:19:04.013
Because you wrote it.

375
00:19:04.081 --> 00:19:05.314
Look at that handwriting.

376
00:19:05.382 --> 00:19:08.284
It matches the note.

377
00:19:08.352 --> 00:19:11.054
"I'm sorry
I have to leave you"?

378
00:19:11.121 --> 00:19:12.922
You were saying good-bye...

379
00:19:12.990 --> 00:19:14.657
To whom?

380
00:19:14.725 --> 00:19:17.393
To my first husband.

381
00:19:17.461 --> 00:19:20.897
I wanted to explain.
but I was too afraid.

382
00:19:20.964 --> 00:19:22.398
I never gave it to him.

383
00:19:22.466 --> 00:19:27.704
But I knew he'd never
stop looking for me. so...

384
00:19:27.771 --> 00:19:28.971
I found another way.

385
00:19:29.039 --> 00:19:31.207
Like faking your own death?

386
00:19:37.815 --> 00:19:39.849
You're Penny Driscoll.

387
00:19:39.917 --> 00:19:42.585
The Reverend's dead wife.

388
00:19:46.390 --> 00:19:48.591
The boys. they're all gone.

389
00:19:48.659 --> 00:19:51.794
They've been kidnapped.

390
00:19:57.134 --> 00:19:59.869
I found some tire tracks
from a truck down by the cove.

391
00:19:59.937 --> 00:20:02.505
Whoever took the boys
must have gone out that way.

392
00:20:02.573 --> 00:20:05.341
Driscoll has them.
He probably plans to cure them.

393
00:20:05.409 --> 00:20:07.376
He hasn't had much
success with that lately.

394
00:20:07.444 --> 00:20:09.112
No.

395
00:20:09.179 --> 00:20:11.047
By tomorrow the boys
won't be able to breathe air.

396
00:20:11.115 --> 00:20:14.117
If we don't get them back.
they will all die!

397
00:20:20.893 --> 00:20:24.429
Edmond Driscoll was certainly
never an easy man to live with.

398
00:20:24.549 --> 00:20:27.298
At first it was an intensity

399
00:20:27.366 --> 00:20:30.334
I was attracted to.
but once we came to Haven...

400
00:20:30.402 --> 00:20:32.970
That passion
I thought I admired

401
00:20:33.038 --> 00:20:35.373
became so dark...

402
00:20:35.441 --> 00:20:36.707
An obsession.

403
00:20:36.775 --> 00:20:38.776
The troubles.

404
00:20:38.844 --> 00:20:41.712
It brought out
such a terrible anger in him.

405
00:20:41.780 --> 00:20:42.780
I knew it was
a matter of time

406
00:20:42.848 --> 00:20:44.348
before he turned it on me.

407
00:20:44.416 --> 00:20:46.451
He didn't abuse you. did he?

408
00:20:46.518 --> 00:20:47.852
Not physically.

409
00:20:47.920 --> 00:20:51.122
It was more subtle than that.

410
00:20:51.190 --> 00:20:54.125
I was young. naive.
I thought that

411
00:20:54.193 --> 00:20:56.461
if I just tried harder.
the man I first met

412
00:20:56.528 --> 00:20:57.895
would come back to me.

413
00:20:57.963 --> 00:20:59.330
But he never did.

414
00:20:59.398 --> 00:21:02.166
Cole was so different
from Edmund. so kind.

415
00:21:02.234 --> 00:21:04.502
When Edmund found out
I was having an affair.

416
00:21:04.570 --> 00:21:07.071
I actually thought
he'd kill me.

417
00:21:26.959 --> 00:21:29.260
Hey. Reverend.

418
00:21:29.328 --> 00:21:30.828
Ms. Ryan.

419
00:21:30.896 --> 00:21:32.396
I told you. call me Evi.

420
00:21:32.464 --> 00:21:34.632
Evi.

421
00:21:36.802 --> 00:21:38.903
Listen. if Reverend Driscoll
has the children.

422
00:21:38.971 --> 00:21:40.438
we're going to
have to reason with him.

423
00:21:40.506 --> 00:21:42.440
There's no reasoning
with Driscoll.

424
00:21:42.508 --> 00:21:43.908
Never was.

425
00:21:43.976 --> 00:21:45.710
Well. then we need to
convince Mary to help us.

426
00:21:45.777 --> 00:21:47.545
She's not gonna want to
watch her son die.

427
00:21:47.613 --> 00:21:49.547
She believes
what Driscoll taught her.

428
00:21:49.615 --> 00:21:51.916
Better dead than cursed.

429
00:21:51.984 --> 00:21:53.217
We'll go to Driscoll.

430
00:21:53.285 --> 00:21:54.852
Make him give
us our children!

431
00:21:54.920 --> 00:21:57.054
No. the Rev has
men of his own.

432
00:21:57.122 --> 00:22:00.091
They'll be ready for you.

433
00:22:42.801 --> 00:22:44.268
Simon Crocker?

434
00:22:44.336 --> 00:22:46.938
They killed my dad?

435
00:22:47.005 --> 00:22:48.806
What are you doing here?

436
00:22:48.874 --> 00:22:52.743
What are <i>you</i> doing here?

437
00:22:52.811 --> 00:22:55.046
What is this?

438
00:22:55.113 --> 00:22:57.014
What?

439
00:22:57.082 --> 00:23:00.218
Oh. this is...

440
00:23:00.285 --> 00:23:02.687
It's my grocery list.
I was gonna go to the...

441
00:23:02.754 --> 00:23:04.889
- Uh-huh. and the Rev's
just storing it

442
00:23:04.957 --> 00:23:07.024
in his office for you.

443
00:23:07.092 --> 00:23:08.359
You know what?
Boys. not now.

444
00:23:08.427 --> 00:23:10.027
Listen.

445
00:23:10.095 --> 00:23:11.729
We think the Rev might
be involved in a kidnapping.

446
00:23:11.797 --> 00:23:15.032
Do you have any idea
where he is?

447
00:23:15.100 --> 00:23:18.603
I know exactly where he is.

448
00:23:26.311 --> 00:23:30.514
Thank you.

449
00:23:36.822 --> 00:23:38.556
Reverend Edmund Driscoll.

450
00:23:38.624 --> 00:23:41.692
You're under arrest
for kidnapping.

451
00:23:41.760 --> 00:23:43.594
Don't even think about it.

452
00:23:43.662 --> 00:23:45.563
All right. guys. stop.

453
00:23:45.631 --> 00:23:47.965
Let's find out
what this is all about.

454
00:23:48.033 --> 00:23:49.900
This is about taking
those Glendower boys

455
00:23:49.968 --> 00:23:51.102
from the compound.

456
00:23:51.169 --> 00:23:53.070
Glendowers?

457
00:23:53.138 --> 00:23:55.273
I haven't been anywhere
near the Glendowers.

458
00:23:55.340 --> 00:23:56.574
I've been right here
all morning.

459
00:23:56.642 --> 00:23:59.810
Actually he has.
the boat was late.

460
00:23:59.878 --> 00:24:01.112
Yeah. thanks for telling me.

461
00:24:01.179 --> 00:24:03.881
Thanks for
checking your messages.

462
00:24:05.684 --> 00:24:07.184
Oh... oh. right.

463
00:24:07.252 --> 00:24:08.653
See. my really good friends.

464
00:24:08.720 --> 00:24:10.321
they call me Evi Crocker.

465
00:24:14.793 --> 00:24:17.461
Then Mary has them.

466
00:24:17.529 --> 00:24:18.896
Where is she?

467
00:24:18.964 --> 00:24:22.366
I have no idea.

468
00:24:35.747 --> 00:24:36.814
What's happened?

469
00:24:36.882 --> 00:24:38.716
Evi!
Evi. get off the dock!

470
00:24:38.784 --> 00:24:39.884
- Where'd they go?
- You gotta help...

471
00:24:39.951 --> 00:24:41.485
Get him outta here!
Quick!

472
00:24:41.553 --> 00:24:42.887
Get him outta here quick!

473
00:24:49.928 --> 00:24:53.164
Give him to me!

474
00:24:53.231 --> 00:24:55.866
Sorry...

475
00:24:55.986 --> 00:24:57.835
But I saw him first.

476
00:24:57.903 --> 00:24:59.870
- He has our children.
- No.

477
00:24:59.938 --> 00:25:01.405
He doesn't.

478
00:25:01.473 --> 00:25:04.008
You're just saying that
to keep him alive.

479
00:25:04.076 --> 00:25:09.046
No. Cole.
I'm trying to help you.

480
00:25:09.114 --> 00:25:11.749
You said you trusted
my father?

481
00:25:11.817 --> 00:25:16.687
Well. you need
to trust me now.

482
00:25:16.755 --> 00:25:17.822
The men are drowning.

483
00:25:17.889 --> 00:25:22.626
They're drowning!

484
00:25:22.694 --> 00:25:25.429
Let them go!

485
00:25:31.970 --> 00:25:33.304
Let's go.

486
00:25:37.642 --> 00:25:40.711
If our children die.

487
00:25:40.779 --> 00:25:43.881
for as long
as we're underwater.

488
00:25:43.949 --> 00:25:45.616
the beaches and docks
of this town

489
00:25:45.684 --> 00:25:50.287
will run red with your blood!

490
00:25:50.355 --> 00:25:58.237
Now you see
the kind of people those...

491
00:25:52.591 --> 00:25:53.858
Unh!

492
00:25:53.925 --> 00:25:55.226
You don't wanna know
how close I was

493
00:25:55.293 --> 00:25:56.727
to letting them take you.

494
00:25:56.795 --> 00:25:58.217
Nathan.

495
00:26:05.437 --> 00:26:07.905
Mary's called him
three times in the past hour.

496
00:26:07.973 --> 00:26:09.573
She wanted to meet with me.

497
00:26:09.641 --> 00:26:11.041
She didn't say why.

498
00:26:11.109 --> 00:26:13.344
You told Mary about
the Glendowers' affliction

499
00:26:13.412 --> 00:26:14.945
and what would happen to Daniel
and the other children.

500
00:26:15.013 --> 00:26:16.781
She deserved to know.

501
00:26:16.848 --> 00:26:20.618
So she took the children.

502
00:26:20.685 --> 00:26:23.954
Where?

503
00:26:24.022 --> 00:26:27.591
Well. I would be happy
to punch him if you won't.

504
00:26:27.659 --> 00:26:29.460
When I was
talking with Mary earlier.

505
00:26:29.528 --> 00:26:32.229
she said there was a barn
just outside town.

506
00:26:32.297 --> 00:26:33.497
The farmer there lets

507
00:26:33.565 --> 00:26:37.234
the food bank
store supplies there.

508
00:26:37.302 --> 00:26:38.769
You're gonna talk to Mary.

509
00:26:38.837 --> 00:26:40.871
Tell her to give us the kids.
tell her you were wrong.

510
00:26:40.939 --> 00:26:44.775
No. I'm not gonna do that.

511
00:26:44.843 --> 00:26:47.845
Then you condemned
those children to death.

512
00:26:50.932 --> 00:26:52.166
The children are so weak.

513
00:26:52.233 --> 00:26:53.801
they are barely
able to stand. Reverend.

514
00:26:53.868 --> 00:26:57.071
Please come here soon.

515
00:27:00.342 --> 00:27:02.209
Everything will be all right.

516
00:27:03.578 --> 00:27:05.646
Reverend Driscoll
will be here soon.

517
00:27:05.714 --> 00:27:08.749
You shouldn't have tricked us
into coming here.

518
00:27:08.817 --> 00:27:10.217
You lied.

519
00:27:10.285 --> 00:27:11.785
I know I did. honey.

520
00:27:11.853 --> 00:27:13.153
But I had to.

521
00:27:13.221 --> 00:27:15.289
You'll understand someday.

522
00:27:15.357 --> 00:27:17.691
I don't wanna die.

523
00:27:17.759 --> 00:27:19.727
You are not gonna die.

524
00:27:19.794 --> 00:27:23.030
I would never let
anything happen to you.

525
00:27:23.098 --> 00:27:26.300
Dad said you
wouldn't understand.

526
00:27:26.368 --> 00:27:28.936
That you wouldn't love us
if you knew.

527
00:27:29.004 --> 00:27:31.305
Dan. that's silly.

528
00:27:31.373 --> 00:27:35.376
Because I love you so much.

529
00:27:35.443 --> 00:27:37.144
And when
Reverend Driscoll cures you.

530
00:27:37.212 --> 00:27:39.513
everything is gonna
go back to normal.

531
00:27:39.581 --> 00:27:41.015
You won't have to leave.

532
00:27:41.082 --> 00:27:44.318
None of you will!

533
00:27:44.386 --> 00:27:46.420
But what if he can't. mom?

534
00:27:46.488 --> 00:27:48.722
Then I will
find somebody who can.

535
00:27:48.790 --> 00:27:50.090
A doctor maybe.

536
00:27:50.158 --> 00:27:51.625
There's got to be someone.

537
00:27:53.762 --> 00:27:55.496
I'm not gonna lose you.

538
00:27:55.563 --> 00:27:58.399
You have to
let us go back. mom.

539
00:27:58.466 --> 00:28:02.036
Please. just do it for me.

540
00:28:16.918 --> 00:28:20.154
Daniel. stay down.

541
00:28:20.221 --> 00:28:24.158
All of you. just stay down!

542
00:28:41.609 --> 00:28:42.543
Stay away!

543
00:28:42.610 --> 00:28:44.845
I have a gun!

544
00:28:44.913 --> 00:28:46.714
Great.

545
00:28:46.781 --> 00:28:48.182
She's not gonna use it.

546
00:28:48.249 --> 00:28:50.617
She's desperate though.
and that's unpredictable.

547
00:28:50.685 --> 00:28:52.086
Maybe we can
go around back.

548
00:28:52.153 --> 00:28:53.554
No. no. no.

549
00:28:53.621 --> 00:28:55.055
We don't know where
she's hidden the kids. okay?

550
00:28:55.123 --> 00:28:58.358
We don't wanna put them
in the line of fire. just...

551
00:28:58.426 --> 00:28:59.626
Mary.

552
00:28:59.694 --> 00:29:01.862
Mary. please.
we just want to talk.

553
00:29:01.930 --> 00:29:05.032
I will only talk
to Reverend Driscoll.

554
00:29:11.773 --> 00:29:14.975
- I'm here. Mary.
- Please. Reverend!

555
00:29:15.043 --> 00:29:17.277
Help us!
The children are sick!

556
00:29:17.345 --> 00:29:20.247
I'll be right there. Mary.

557
00:29:20.315 --> 00:29:23.250
You want me to get her
to release those children?

558
00:29:23.318 --> 00:29:25.252
I want something
from you in return.

559
00:29:25.320 --> 00:29:26.587
Surprise.

560
00:29:26.654 --> 00:29:28.622
I want to see you both
at Sunday services.

561
00:29:28.690 --> 00:29:30.290
I want the town to see

562
00:29:30.358 --> 00:29:34.027
that we stand together.

563
00:29:34.095 --> 00:29:37.464
Not a chance.

564
00:29:42.170 --> 00:29:44.404
Well. then
I'm not goin' in there.

565
00:29:44.472 --> 00:29:45.539
Heh.

566
00:29:47.642 --> 00:29:49.109
Yep.

567
00:29:49.177 --> 00:29:50.611
All right. Mike. bring 'em up.

568
00:30:13.234 --> 00:30:14.668
Penny?

569
00:30:14.736 --> 00:30:16.617
Hello. Edmond.

570
00:30:19.274 --> 00:30:22.009
Is this some kind of trick?

571
00:30:22.076 --> 00:30:25.345
No. it's really me.

572
00:30:25.413 --> 00:30:28.732
All these years
I thought you were dead.

573
00:30:28.852 --> 00:30:32.452
- I did what I had to do.
- You left me.

574
00:30:32.520 --> 00:30:34.955
And our daughter?

575
00:30:35.023 --> 00:30:36.323
You think
I wanted to leave her?

576
00:30:36.391 --> 00:30:37.324
Oh. just so you
could be with that...

577
00:30:37.392 --> 00:30:39.860
Man!

578
00:30:39.928 --> 00:30:41.929
Cole may be troubled.
but he's still a man.

579
00:30:41.996 --> 00:30:43.697
A human being like you and I

580
00:30:43.765 --> 00:30:45.966
and no amount of prayer
or hurting innocent people

581
00:30:46.034 --> 00:30:49.102
is going to
take the troubles away.

582
00:30:52.173 --> 00:30:55.509
You only say that
because you don't believe.

583
00:30:55.577 --> 00:30:57.945
Yeah. you never believed.

584
00:30:58.012 --> 00:31:00.080
What I believe... what I know
is that these children

585
00:31:00.148 --> 00:31:03.116
didn't harm
or do anything wrong.

586
00:31:03.184 --> 00:31:06.720
And if you don't get Mary
to release them. they'll die.

587
00:31:06.788 --> 00:31:09.122
Even you can't
want revenge that badly.

588
00:31:09.190 --> 00:31:10.524
This isn't about revenge.

589
00:31:10.592 --> 00:31:11.792
Yes. it is.

590
00:31:11.860 --> 00:31:13.527
You've convinced
your followers.

591
00:31:13.595 --> 00:31:15.028
you may even have
convinced yourself

592
00:31:15.096 --> 00:31:17.231
that you hate the cursed
because they're evil.

593
00:31:17.298 --> 00:31:20.334
You hate them because
27 years ago it was your anger.

594
00:31:20.401 --> 00:31:24.171
your bigotry
that drove me away.

595
00:31:24.239 --> 00:31:29.743
What you decide to do here today
isn't about the troubles.

596
00:31:29.811 --> 00:31:33.413
It's about you.

597
00:31:45.159 --> 00:31:46.827
Mary.

598
00:31:46.895 --> 00:31:49.496
It's me.

599
00:32:07.548 --> 00:32:08.749
We have to go in.

600
00:32:08.816 --> 00:32:10.284
They screwed us.

601
00:32:10.351 --> 00:32:12.141
I know it.

602
00:32:16.624 --> 00:32:17.858
Parker.

603
00:32:39.747 --> 00:32:41.181
Thank you.

604
00:32:41.249 --> 00:32:43.517
That was really brave.

605
00:32:43.584 --> 00:32:45.619
Oh. Mary would
never have shot me.

606
00:32:45.687 --> 00:32:47.988
No. I meant convincing her

607
00:32:48.056 --> 00:32:50.691
that this about
more than just prayer.

608
00:32:50.758 --> 00:32:53.460
You're right about that.
Officer Parker.

609
00:32:53.528 --> 00:32:56.318
The time for prayer
is indeed over.

610
00:32:58.399 --> 00:33:00.467
But a good Shepherd
always finds a way

611
00:33:00.535 --> 00:33:02.818
to save his flock.

612
00:33:05.740 --> 00:33:07.541
Are you sure?

613
00:33:07.608 --> 00:33:10.243
Thanks.

614
00:33:19.187 --> 00:33:23.357
Bangor just sent over
Leith's autopsy results.

615
00:33:23.424 --> 00:33:25.659
There's no water in his lungs.

616
00:33:25.727 --> 00:33:26.860
So he didn't drown?

617
00:33:26.928 --> 00:33:29.496
No. and some bruising came up.

618
00:33:29.564 --> 00:33:32.199
Looks pre-mortem.

619
00:33:32.266 --> 00:33:35.268
Leith was murdered.

620
00:33:52.270 --> 00:33:53.804
Thank you again for your help.

621
00:33:53.872 --> 00:33:55.840
Don't thank us yet.

622
00:33:55.907 --> 00:34:01.178
Leith's death
wasn't a suicide.

623
00:34:01.246 --> 00:34:03.460
Cole murdered him.

624
00:34:05.984 --> 00:34:07.084
How did you know?

625
00:34:07.152 --> 00:34:09.353
Daniel told us that he saw

626
00:34:09.421 --> 00:34:11.255
Leith and Cole
arguing that night.

627
00:34:11.323 --> 00:34:13.591
That Leith had told him
he had found a way to make sure

628
00:34:13.658 --> 00:34:16.227
his mother had money
until they came back.

629
00:34:16.294 --> 00:34:21.165
What he didn't tell Daniel
was it was blackmail.

630
00:34:21.233 --> 00:34:23.634
Leith was gonna
sell your note to the Rev.

631
00:34:23.702 --> 00:34:25.069
tell him where you were.

632
00:34:25.136 --> 00:34:27.271
Offer up the note as proof.

633
00:34:27.339 --> 00:34:28.505
Driscoll would have come

634
00:34:28.573 --> 00:34:30.908
when I wasn't
here to protect her.

635
00:34:30.976 --> 00:34:33.444
He would have turned the town
against all our women.

636
00:34:33.511 --> 00:34:35.446
How could any of them
have survived?

637
00:34:35.513 --> 00:34:36.981
I'm so sorry.

638
00:34:37.048 --> 00:34:38.082
It's all my fault.

639
00:34:38.149 --> 00:34:41.719
No. no. no. no.
it was my choice.

640
00:34:41.786 --> 00:34:43.087
I had to keep you safe.

641
00:34:43.154 --> 00:34:45.990
But you can't take him to jail.

642
00:34:46.057 --> 00:34:48.993
No.

643
00:34:49.060 --> 00:34:50.995
Bringing him in
would be a death sentence.

644
00:34:51.062 --> 00:34:52.997
I know that.

645
00:34:53.064 --> 00:34:56.000
You'll stay on the compound.

646
00:34:56.067 --> 00:34:59.536
Stay safe.

647
00:34:59.604 --> 00:35:01.772
And I'll wait for you.

648
00:35:01.840 --> 00:35:04.975
No matter how long it takes.

649
00:35:16.021 --> 00:35:18.422
I know you thought
you had good reason

650
00:35:18.490 --> 00:35:20.958
for killing Leith.

651
00:35:21.026 --> 00:35:23.394
What you did was murder. Cole.

652
00:35:23.461 --> 00:35:26.597
And when the troubles are over.

653
00:35:26.665 --> 00:35:29.266
I'll come to you

654
00:35:29.334 --> 00:35:32.303
and pay for my crime.

655
00:35:32.370 --> 00:35:34.405
But until then...

656
00:35:34.472 --> 00:35:36.907
You'll watch after my family?

657
00:35:36.975 --> 00:35:40.110
Keep Driscoll away?

658
00:35:40.178 --> 00:35:43.180
Yes.

659
00:35:47.415 --> 00:35:50.563
Can you tell me about Lucy?

660
00:35:52.424 --> 00:35:55.092
Lucy was only in Haven
a few months.

661
00:35:55.160 --> 00:35:56.660
Garland Wuornos
would've known more.

662
00:35:56.728 --> 00:35:58.028
they worked together.

663
00:35:58.096 --> 00:35:59.763
Helped people
who no one else could help.

664
00:35:59.831 --> 00:36:01.398
Did she say anything
about where she was going

665
00:36:01.466 --> 00:36:03.500
after she left Haven?

666
00:36:03.568 --> 00:36:04.702
No.

667
00:36:04.769 --> 00:36:05.836
Just like she appeared one day.

668
00:36:05.904 --> 00:36:07.886
she was gone.

669
00:36:10.742 --> 00:36:14.311
It was a few days after
the Colorado Kid murder.

670
00:36:14.379 --> 00:36:15.913
I have a picture of her
there on the beach

671
00:36:15.981 --> 00:36:18.082
where they found him.

672
00:36:18.149 --> 00:36:21.185
It was the only time
that anyone ever...

673
00:36:21.252 --> 00:36:23.253
saw her cry.

674
00:36:38.979 --> 00:36:41.005
Wait!

675
00:36:41.072 --> 00:36:42.206
Before you go.

676
00:36:42.273 --> 00:36:44.008
You need to tell me.

677
00:36:44.075 --> 00:36:46.076
Your tattoo. what does it mean?

678
00:36:46.144 --> 00:36:48.112
When Reverend Driscoll
and others like him

679
00:36:48.179 --> 00:36:49.279
come for us.

680
00:36:49.347 --> 00:36:50.848
there are those who will fight.

681
00:36:50.915 --> 00:36:52.549
Do you know me?

682
00:36:52.617 --> 00:36:54.184
Do you know why
they want me dead?

683
00:36:54.252 --> 00:36:55.319
All I know is
you're being watched

684
00:36:55.387 --> 00:36:57.388
in case you decide to follow

685
00:36:57.455 --> 00:36:59.023
in your father's footsteps.

686
00:36:59.090 --> 00:37:02.092
Is that why
one of you killed him?

687
00:37:02.160 --> 00:37:04.328
Simon Crocker.

688
00:37:04.396 --> 00:37:05.662
Do you remember?

689
00:37:05.730 --> 00:37:07.314
I don't know
who killed your father.

690
00:37:07.434 --> 00:37:08.561
But if you wanna stay alive.

691
00:37:08.681 --> 00:37:11.361
I suggest you stay
out of his business.

692
00:37:32.190 --> 00:37:34.825
Are you sure we're
doing the right thing?

693
00:37:34.893 --> 00:37:36.160
After everything
you've seen.

694
00:37:36.227 --> 00:37:38.162
you can even ask me that?

695
00:37:38.229 --> 00:37:40.597
- I know...
- You're sure...

696
00:37:40.665 --> 00:37:44.435
Duke doesn't
suspect anything?

697
00:37:44.502 --> 00:37:46.070
No.

698
00:37:46.137 --> 00:37:49.706
He fell for me getting you
away from the church. didn't he?

699
00:37:49.774 --> 00:37:53.343
And now that he knows
his father was murdered.

700
00:37:53.411 --> 00:37:55.746
you've got him.

701
00:38:07.219 --> 00:38:09.320
Your uncles and cousins
are gonna take care of you.

702
00:38:09.388 --> 00:38:10.888
I'm not scared.

703
00:38:10.956 --> 00:38:11.989
Good.

704
00:38:12.057 --> 00:38:13.758
'Cause I'm gonna be here.

705
00:38:13.826 --> 00:38:15.560
And I'm gonna love you
and I'm gonna think about you

706
00:38:15.627 --> 00:38:19.664
every minute
until you come home.

707
00:38:19.731 --> 00:38:21.999
I'll miss you too. mom.

708
00:38:22.067 --> 00:38:27.305
♪ Cold is the cry that rings ♪

709
00:38:27.372 --> 00:38:29.340
Come on. Daniel.

710
00:38:29.408 --> 00:38:34.812
♪ From this far distant shore ♪

711
00:38:38.417 --> 00:38:41.786
♪ winter ♪

712
00:38:41.854 --> 00:38:46.524
♪ has come too late ♪

713
00:38:46.592 --> 00:38:49.460
It gets easier.

714
00:38:49.528 --> 00:38:51.896
Let us help you. Mary.

715
00:38:51.964 --> 00:38:57.335
♪ Too close beside me ♪

716
00:38:57.402 --> 00:39:00.605
♪ how can I ♪

717
00:39:00.672 --> 00:39:05.476
♪ chase away ♪

718
00:39:05.544 --> 00:39:12.001
♪ all these fears deep inside ♪

719
00:39:14.987 --> 00:39:18.322
♪ I'll wait ♪

720
00:39:18.390 --> 00:39:23.194
♪ for the signs to come ♪

721
00:39:23.262 --> 00:39:28.699
♪ I'll find a way ♪

722
00:39:28.767 --> 00:39:32.537
♪ I will wait
the time to come ♪

723
00:39:32.604 --> 00:39:37.074
It's beautiful in a way.

724
00:39:37.142 --> 00:39:38.709
But it's so sad.

725
00:39:38.777 --> 00:39:42.680
They don't even know
how long they'll be gone.

726
00:39:42.748 --> 00:39:46.217
A whole family just...

727
00:39:46.285 --> 00:39:49.921
Split in two.

728
00:39:49.988 --> 00:39:52.623
United by secrets.

729
00:39:52.691 --> 00:39:57.094
I wanted to learn more
about the Chief.

730
00:39:57.162 --> 00:39:59.864
But there's so much
he didn't tell me. so...

731
00:39:59.932 --> 00:40:04.735
I didn't even know
the right questions to ask.

732
00:40:04.803 --> 00:40:09.040
Gwen also told me
that your father and Lucy...

733
00:40:09.107 --> 00:40:12.109
Helped a lot
of troubled people.

734
00:40:14.513 --> 00:40:19.984
♪ As I sail home to you ♪

735
00:40:20.052 --> 00:40:21.586
Looks like we've
been following

736
00:40:21.653 --> 00:40:26.591
in their footsteps
without even knowing it.

737
00:40:38.148 --> 00:40:42.645
